1
00:00:50,341 --> 00:00:54,888
DIVORCE ATTORNEY SHIN

2
00:00:56,681 --> 00:01:00,101
Domestic case number 2022-523845.

3
00:01:00,185 --> 00:01:02,270
Plaintiff, Kang Hui-seop.
Defendant, Lee Seo-jin.

4
00:01:02,353 --> 00:01:06,608
Plaintiff's complaint. Plaintiff's brief
submitted on May 3, 2022.

5
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:10,653
Plaintiff will testify based on the brief
submitted on June 6, 2022,

6
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:13,823
and exhibits 1 to 12 have been submitted.

7
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:16,076
I have a question.

8
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:20,497
Do you remember
that link I sent you that day?

9
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:23,833
The best restaurant nearby.

10
00:01:24,709 --> 00:01:25,835
Did you go?

11
00:01:28,671 --> 00:01:31,633
-Yes.
-Not bad, right?

12
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:41,768
Yes, it was all right.

13
00:01:43,102 --> 00:01:45,188
It's a shame
that she was unwilling to negotiate

14
00:01:45,271 --> 00:01:48,191
throughout the mediation period.

15
00:01:48,274 --> 00:01:51,611
It is quite disconcerting to see
Ms. Lee demanding custody

16
00:01:51,694 --> 00:01:54,656
even though she is the spouse at fault

17
00:01:54,739 --> 00:01:58,118
and her son was sent to the emergency room
in the middle of the night.

18
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:02,080
Would any decent parent
be able to make such a decision

19
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:05,542
when the reason for their divorce
is causing so much pain for their son?

20
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:08,503
This is causing Hyeon-u so much pain.

21
00:02:09,337 --> 00:02:11,756
Should I really keep fighting
for his custody?

22
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:14,676
DONGSEON UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

23
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:16,302
Why do you want Hyeon-u's custody?

24
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:19,681
Just like you said,

25
00:02:19,764 --> 00:02:22,016
this is putting him in a really bad place.

26
00:02:23,059 --> 00:02:24,352
Why do you want his custody?

27
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,023
Because he can't stay there.

28
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:32,819
So you're afraid that Hyeon-u will
live in pain just like you did, right?

29
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:34,571
Yes.

30
00:02:34,654 --> 00:02:37,657
That's why we have to win this lawsuit.

31
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:39,033
And we will.

32
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:41,578
Now that we're going to court,

33
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:44,455
we'll also demand
an exact division of property.

34
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:45,790
Don't do that.

35
00:02:46,791 --> 00:02:48,334
He might become more stubborn.

36
00:02:48,418 --> 00:02:51,880
Do you think he'll hand over the boy
just because you don't demand money?

37
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:53,798
You'd just be taking what's yours.

38
00:02:55,049 --> 00:02:55,925
Also,

39
00:02:57,343 --> 00:02:58,344
don't be so scared.

40
00:02:59,137 --> 00:03:00,138
We're going to win.

41
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:03,766
Let's wait and see who'll win.

42
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:13,276
Giving Ms. Lee the custody
of her son would be the same

43
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:15,820
as giving up on the dignity of the child.

44
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:19,616
It is only natural for my client
to not give up his custody.

45
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:25,038
-Defendant's counselor.
-Yes.

46
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:26,456
His dignity?

47
00:03:27,206 --> 00:03:28,666
It's interesting you'd say that.

48
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,667
Make your case.

49
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:31,711
Have you ever asked Kang Hyeon-u,

50
00:03:31,794 --> 00:03:35,423
the child under discussion,
who he wants to live with?

51
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:38,426
Your Honor, the child's opinion
isn't taken into account

52
00:03:38,509 --> 00:03:41,179
-unless he is over 13--
-I know that.

53
00:03:41,262 --> 00:03:43,014
Anyone can look that up online.

54
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:45,934
A child has to be 13
for their opinion to be considered.

55
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:47,101
But that's not what I'm asking.

56
00:03:48,436 --> 00:03:49,646
Mr. Kang.

57
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:53,566
Your child's opinion
can't affect the court's decision,

58
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:56,861
but you could have
asked him as his father, right?

59
00:03:58,279 --> 00:03:59,405
We are here

60
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:03,952
because the child already said
he couldn't live with a mom like her.

61
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:05,286
Is that so?

62
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:08,957
In that case, one of us has been lied to.

63
00:04:25,056 --> 00:04:25,890
Hyeon-u.

64
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:27,767
The way I see it…

65
00:04:30,186 --> 00:04:32,605
both your dad and your mom are at fault.

66
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:36,901
They're both awful parents.

67
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:41,364
You'll have to deal with that.

68
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,116
It sucks.

69
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:45,201
Move out as soon as you come of age.

70
00:04:45,868 --> 00:04:48,246
Living alone isn't all that bad.

71
00:04:49,872 --> 00:04:50,999
But let me ask you.

72
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,001
If…

73
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:58,589
If you could choose just one person

74
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:01,551
to be left in this world with you,

75
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:04,012
who would you choose?

76
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:07,432
Mom.

77
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:10,768
Okay.

78
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:14,397
I thought she might die.

79
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:18,318
She would stand barefoot
on the balcony sometimes

80
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:20,403
when she thought no one was watching.

81
00:05:22,113 --> 00:05:23,614
But I saw her.

82
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:25,908
It must have been scary.

83
00:05:26,534 --> 00:05:28,661
She was in pain.

84
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:30,496
I'm in pain too.

85
00:05:31,205 --> 00:05:32,081
I know.

86
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:33,958
You're in the worst pain right now.

87
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:37,754
I saw something painful.

88
00:05:44,343 --> 00:05:46,846
So when will you move out, Hyeon-u?

89
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:48,931
I moved to Germany

90
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:51,017
-in high school--
-You already know, right?

91
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,021
You know why I threw Dad's phone.

92
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:05,490
Hyeon-u.

93
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:10,328
What you saw and heard…

94
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:13,581
That won't go away.

95
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:15,750
For all your life,

96
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:19,545
it'll linger in your heart, mind,
and all over the place.

97
00:06:20,671 --> 00:06:24,425
And it will only get better
if you try your absolute best.

98
00:06:25,093 --> 00:06:27,929
If it keeps coming back,
you have to keep yourself busy.

99
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:31,933
Whenever that happens to me,
I listen to music.

100
00:06:32,683 --> 00:06:33,810
Trot music.

101
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:43,319
I have a question.

102
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:48,032
But you don't have to answer it
if it's too hard for you.

103
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:48,991
Okay?

104
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:55,623
Did you look it up?

105
00:06:58,835 --> 00:07:00,294
Or did someone show it to you?

106
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:08,261
Your Honor.

107
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:11,222
This is Hyeon-u's journal.

108
00:07:12,014 --> 00:07:14,684
Your Honor, this evidence
was not submitted beforehand.

109
00:07:14,767 --> 00:07:17,311
-No, I received it today.
-Let's hear it.

110
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:24,444
"I'm unhappy."

111
00:07:25,027 --> 00:07:27,321
"Mom is never home."

112
00:07:27,405 --> 00:07:29,699
"I'm always with Dad these days."

113
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:32,827
"That's why I'm unhappy."

114
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:36,247
"I'm always with Dad,
who makes me unhappy."

115
00:07:36,747 --> 00:07:37,957
"I pity myself."

116
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:41,752
Your Honor, Hyeon-u is
currently in a mental state

117
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:44,088
where he is unhappy about everything.

118
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:47,216
A child's unstable emotional state
cannot be used as legal grounds.

119
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,342
She's right.

120
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:49,760
She's absolutely right.

121
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:51,137
An unstable child.

122
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:53,389
Your Honor.

123
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:55,683
I would like to question
the plaintiff, Kang Hui-seop.

124
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:57,477
You may proceed.

125
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:08,738
WITNESS

126
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:11,449
Mr. Kang.

127
00:08:13,117 --> 00:08:14,535
Did you show Hyeon-u,

128
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:16,954
your insecure son…

129
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,585
the video of Ms. Lee?

130
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:25,922
Your Honor!

131
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:28,841
This is only causing
humiliation for my client!

132
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:31,177
It's an important question.
I will hear his answer.

133
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:32,720
Let me ask once again.

134
00:08:34,138 --> 00:08:36,140
Did you show that video

135
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:38,059
to your young son,

136
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:40,394
Hyeon-u,

137
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,855
who's only in third grade?

138
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:45,233
What?

139
00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:46,275
What did you say?

140
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:49,362
I want to live with Mom.

141
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:50,446
Have you gone insane?

142
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,324
Do you have any idea what a bitch she is?

143
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:56,452
I want to live with Mom.

144
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,621
I want to live with her.

145
00:08:59,247 --> 00:09:00,957
Please.

146
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,250
Watch this.

147
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:03,584
Watch it, you little shit!

148
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:04,794
Open your eyes!

149
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:06,837
This is who your mother is.

150
00:09:06,921 --> 00:09:07,880
Look!

151
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:08,965
Look at it!

152
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,094
He had to know.

153
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:17,473
He had to know why he couldn't live
with his so-called mom!

154
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,308
Plaintiff, calm down.

155
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:20,643
That's why you showed him?

156
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:26,148
Plaintiff.

157
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:28,401
You should be after that trashy bitch.

158
00:09:28,484 --> 00:09:29,819
Why are you interrogating me?

159
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:31,612
I don't care if you're an attorney.

160
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:34,865
I showed him.

161
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:38,286
He's my son.

162
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:39,996
I showed him as his dad. So what?

163
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:42,123
-Plaintiff, calm down.
-Damn it.

164
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:45,001
What did you say about his dignity?

165
00:09:45,751 --> 00:09:47,128
Your Honor.

166
00:09:47,211 --> 00:09:49,338
Do you think
Mr. Kang's despicable behavior

167
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:52,258
respects his son's dignity?

168
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:01,434
Defendant, sit down.

169
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:17,533
Defendant!

170
00:10:19,035 --> 00:10:20,494
You crazy bitch, have you gone--

171
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:18,094
You're up.

172
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:21,680
So? Are you all right?

173
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:28,270
-Excuse me.
-You have to finish this before you go.

174
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:29,313
Excuse me!

175
00:11:30,439 --> 00:11:31,649
Excuse me!

176
00:11:31,732 --> 00:11:32,733
Ms. Lee.

177
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:35,903
-Yes?
-Please pull this out.

178
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:39,240
-Ma'am, you must finish the IV--
-Please pull it out.

179
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:42,451
Okay.

180
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:45,079
One second. I'll let the doctor know.

181
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,459
Why didn't you tell me?

182
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:54,130
This morning,

183
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:56,424
I got a call from Hyeon-u.

184
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,009
He asked me to come to his school.

185
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:01,303
That's when I got his journal.

186
00:12:02,888 --> 00:12:04,014
He said that…

187
00:12:05,808 --> 00:12:06,851
you would cry

188
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:09,437
if you found out that he had seen it,

189
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:14,233
but he still wanted to live with you.

190
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:24,994
I'll beg for his forgiveness

191
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:28,122
until the day I die.

192
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:32,835
I want to see Hyeon-u.

193
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:34,462
Okay.

194
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:37,923
I'll tell the doctor. Give me one second.

195
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:54,148
Wait.

196
00:12:54,231 --> 00:12:55,900
I forgot to tell you something important.

197
00:12:57,026 --> 00:12:58,152
We won.

198
00:12:58,986 --> 00:13:02,114
Go have a nice meal with Hyeon-u.

199
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:09,997
Thank you.

200
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:40,444
MARRY CAREFULLY
DIVORCE SWIFTLY

201
00:13:43,614 --> 00:13:44,657
Seems like they lost.

202
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,909
Not going to happen.

203
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:48,118
It should be over by now.

204
00:13:48,202 --> 00:13:50,704
-Maybe they're having lunch.
-It's way past lunchtime.

205
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:52,081
Maybe she's consulting him.

206
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:53,499
Because they lost?

207
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:56,126
Why won't he call--

208
00:13:59,713 --> 00:14:00,548
You lost…

209
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:02,258
You won, right?

210
